item.title: Grevillea steiglitziana
item.dc:creator: koolah
item.description: This grevillea is a low spreading shrub with shiny, lightly toothed, holly-like leaves and bright red toothbrush flowers. It is found in Victoria, mostly confined to the Brisbane Ranges between Geelong & Bacchus marsh. Grows in dry, open eucalypt forest
